{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"58d3863a-c6bc-4369-9545-a704317db380","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2 / .NET 9**, so you can use constructor injection for `TestContext` (introduced in MSTest v3). Combine it with `[TestInitialize]` for async setup:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private HttpClient _client = null!;\n\n    // Sync init + TestContext via constructor injection\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    // Async init\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        _client = await CreateAuthenticatedClientAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public void Cleanup() => _client?.Dispose();\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        // use _client ...\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor** — runs first; use for sync setup and `TestContext` injection.\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — supports `async Task`; use for async setup. Runs after the constructor, before each test.\n- Avoid the legacy `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern — constructor injection is cleaner and gives you a `readonly` field.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9719ebf4-68b5-40e0-b702-89cf6848b8a1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), the recommended approach is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: Use constructor injection — `TestContext` can be injected via the constructor (MSTest 3.x+). The old `[TestInitialize]`-based property pattern still works but constructor injection is preferred.\n\n2. **Synchronous init**: Use the constructor or `[TestInitialize]` method.\n\n3. **Async init**: Use `[TestInitialize]` with `async Task` return type. Constructors can't be async, so async initialization must go in `[TestInitialize]`.\n\n\nLet me show a concrete example of how to inject TestContext directly into the constructor.","outputTokens":528,"requestId":"1BD9:315D54:4E1FF9:5931CA:6A03D72E"},"id":"5e652d49-247c-4218-9d93-af6990d0e1ae","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:43:23.992Z","parentId":"16bf8f95-c3ad-4810-990c-2d974eca71e7"}
